The paper deals with convex optimization with noisy zero-th order information, which is a common problem in machine learning and optimization. The focus is on problems with high degrees of smoothness, such as logistic regression, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of high-order smoothness to improve estimation rates, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The algorithms presented in the paper involve optimization and computation, which are relevant to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY).
